---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Maine Cannabis Regulations | Maine Dispensary Guide" description="Complete guide to Maine cannabis regulations, compliance requirements, and legal framework for dispensary owners.">
  <article>
    <header>
      <h1>Cannabis Regulations in Maine</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Understanding the legal framework for operating a dispensary in Maine</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>State Regulatory Framework</h2>
      <p>Maine's cannabis industry is regulated by the Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP), which oversees licensing, compliance, and enforcement for both medical and adult-use cannabis businesses.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Regulations</h2>
      
      <h3>Licensing Requirements</h3>
      <p>All cannabis businesses must obtain the appropriate license from OCP before operating. Licenses must be renewed annually.</p>
      
      <h3>Age Restrictions</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Adult-use customers must be 21 years or older</li>
        <li>Medical dispensaries may serve qualified patients with valid medical cannabis cards</li>
        <li>Caregivers may purchase cannabis on behalf of patients</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3>Possession Limits</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Adult-use: Up to 2.5 ounces of cannabis flower or equivalent concentrates per day</li>
        <li>Medical patients: Up to 5 ounces (with physician certification)</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3>Operating Hours</h3>
      <p>Cannabis dispensaries may operate between 7:00 AM and 9:00 PM, though local ordinances may impose additional restrictions.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Compliance Requirements</h2>
      
      <h3>Seed-to-Sale Tracking</h3>
      <p>All licensees must use the state's approved seed-to-sale tracking system to track all cannabis products from cultivation to sale.</p>
      
      <h3>Packaging & Labeling</h3>
      <p>All products must comply with Maine's strict packaging and labeling requirements:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Child-resistant packaging required</li>
        <li>Label must include THC content, warnings, and producer information</li>
        <li>No marketing to minors</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3>Testing Requirements</h3>
      <p>All cannabis products must be tested by a licensed testing laboratory for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Potency</li>
        <li>Contaminants (pesticides, mold, heavy metals)</li>
        <li>Residual solvents</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3>Security Requirements</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>24/7 video surveillance of all areas</li>
        <li>Alarm systems</li>
        <li>Secure storage for inventory</li>
        <li>Background checks for all employees</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local Regulations</h2>
      <p>Maine municipalities can enact local ordinances regulating or prohibiting cannabis businesses. Before选址, research local zoning laws and whether the town has opted in or out of allowing cannabis businesses.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Ongoing Compliance</h2>
      <p>Dispensaries must maintain compliance through:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Regular inventory audits</li>
        <li>Employee training and documentation</li>
        <li>Maintenance of proper records</li>
        <li>Cooperation with OCP inspections</li>
        <li>Timely license renewal</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This information is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal advice. Regulations change frequently. Consult with a qualified cannabis attorney in Maine for specific guidance.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  header {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  
  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }
  
  section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  
  section h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  
  section h3 {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .disclaimer {
    background: #fff3cd;
    border: 1px solid #ffc107;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }
</style>
